0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bigger%20picture%20here%20is%20that%20SpaceX%20probably%20underestimated%20the%20shielding%20needed%20to%20bolster%20its%20rocket%20from%20the%20power%20of%20its%20own%20engines%2C%20Tripathi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20this%2C%20SpaceX%20has%20likely%20had%20to%20add%20more%20protection%20to%20the%20components%20in%20the%20booster%2C%20Tripathi%20said.%20The%20company%20said%20it%20was%20adding%20more%20systems%20to%20control%20fires%20onboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20adds%20weight%2C%20which%20is%20probably%20why%20SpaceX%20had%20to%20move%20to%20hot%20staging%2C%20per%20Tripathi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20A%20safer%20self-destruct%20system%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWild%20cheers%20let%20off%20by%20SpaceX%20engineers%20fell%20to%20worried%20hushes%20at%20around%202%20minutes%2045%20into%20the%20test%20flight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rocket%20was%20due%20to%20have%20separated%20from%20its%20booster%2C%20but%20it%20had%20clearly%20failed.%20For%20about%20a%20minute%2C%20it%20tumbled%20out%20of%20control%2C%20before%20it%20burst%20into%20a%20huge%20fireball.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20explosion%20didn't%20happen%20immediately%2C%20and%20that%20is%20a%20big%20problem.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side-by-side%20images%20showing%20the%20Starship%20rocket%20tumbling%20at%20time%20stamps%202%3A48%2C%2003%3A03%2C%2003%3A51%2C%20and%20finally%20bursting%20into%20a%20fireball%20at%2003%3A59.%20Arrows%20point%20to%20the%20rocket%20in%20the%20pictures.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65045863b8708d001927a702%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStarship%20was%20seen%20tumbling%20before%20it%20burst%20into%20a%20fireball%20on%20its%20first%20integrated%20flight.%3Cp%3ESpaceX%2FInsider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStarship%20is%20fitted%20with%20a%20self-destruct%20system%2C%20which%20automatically%20detects%20when%20something%20is%20going%20wrong.%20That%20system%20%E2%80%94%20called%20the%20Autonomous%20Flight%20Safety%20System%20(AFSS)%20%E2%80%94%20did%20set%20off%20explosives%20in%20the%20rocket%2C%20but%20only%20after%20an%20%26quot%3Bunexpected%20delay%2C%26quot%3B%20SpaceX%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20September%208.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20the%20AFSS%20system%20did%20not%20work%20as%20it%20should%20have%2C%20a%20matter%20that%20would%20have%20been%20taken%20very%20seriously%20by%20the%20FAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20is%20not%20allowed%20to%20share%20much%20about%20the%20improvements%20for%20security%20reasons%2C%20Tripathi%20said.%20But%20the%20company%20has%20confirmed%20it%20has%20%26quot%3Benhanced%20and%20requalified%20the%20AFSS%20to%20improve%20system%20reliability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0A%20'gigantic%20upside-down%20shower%20head'%20on%20the%20launchpad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side%20by%20side%20annotated%20images%20show%20Starship's%20launchpad%20in%20April%20and%20September%202023.%20An%20arrow%20points%20to%20a%20blue%20tarp%20above%20the%20launchpad%20covering%20SpaceX's%20new%20flooding%20system.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fb220aa39a1b00190ba5c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpaceX%20added%20a%20flooding%20system%20to%20its%20launchpad%20to%20avoid%20fire%20and%20heat%20damage%20(in%20this%20picture%2C%20it%20is%20covered%20with%20a%20blue%20tarp).%3Cp%3ESpaceX%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20its%20April%20launch%2C%20the%20rocket%C2%A0blasted%20through%20its%20launchpad%2C%20sending%20fragments%20of%20concrete%20and%20other%20debris%20flying%20around%20the%20launch%20site%20in%20Boca%20Chica%2C%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20debris%20was%20spread%20across%20385%20acres%2C%20including%20some%20state