0England%20has%20assessed%20the%20present%20circumstances%20and%20offers%20essential%20guidance%20to%20veterinary%20experts%20and%20organisations%20engaged%20in%20the%20import%20of%20dogs%20from%20regions%20where%20Brucella%20canis%20is%20prevalent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20greatest%20risk%20of%20exposure%20is%20potential%20contact%20with%20Brucella%20canis-contaminated%20materials%2C%20especially%20tissues%20and%20fluids%20associated%20with%20breeding%20and%20parturition.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBrucella%20canis%20is%20also%20shed%20in%20a%20dog's%20bodily%20fluids%2C%20such%20as%20urine%2C%20blood%2C%20and%20saliva.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIf%20positive%2C%20a%20dog%20is%20considered%20infected%20for%20life%2C%20even%20after%20antimicrobial%20treatment.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EHuman%20cases%20are%20rarely%20reported%2C%20and%20none%20have%20been%20confirmed%20following%20contact%20with%20an%20infected%20dog%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20dogs%2C%20the%20disease%20is%20untreatable%2C%20and%20government%20guidelines%20advocate%20for%20euthanasia%20as%20the%20recommended%20course%20of%20action.%20However%2C%20for%20humans%2C%20effective%20treatment%20is%20available%20through%20an%20extended%20regimen%20of%20antibiotics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20government%20said%20in%20the%20statement%20about%20the%20disease%20that%20even%20following%20antimicrobial%20treatment%2C%20an%20animal%20is%20considered%20infected%20for%20life%20and%20therefore%20could%20present%20a%20risk%20of%20onward%20infection%20to%20canine%20and%20human%20contacts.%20Thus%2C%20euthanasia%20of%20infected%20dogs%20is%20considered%20the%20only%20way%20to%20completely%20remove%20the%20risk%20of%20onward%20transmission.%20The%20decision%20to%20euthanize%20is%20a%20matter%20for%20the%20owner(s)%20and%20their%20private%20veterinary%20surgeon.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695120060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fe8r15kj_a-disease-typica