3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20is%20supercharging%20Bard%20by%20giving%20it%20access%20to%20its%20most%20popular%20apps.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20a%20big%20leap%20forward%20as%20the%20company%20continues%20to%20chase%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBard%20is%20now%20also%20set%20to%20highlight%20parts%20of%20responses%20that%20may%20be%20hallucinations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20is%20supercharging%20its%20Bard%20AI%20chatbot%20by%20giving%20it%20access%20to%20the%20company's%20most%20popular%20apps%2C%20such%20as%20Gmail%2C%20Maps%2C%20and%20YouTube.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20abilities%20should%20make%20Bard%20significantly%20more%20useful%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-how-big-tech-will-win-again-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderscoring%20Google's%20advantage%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20tapping%20hugely%20popular%20existing%20products%20as%20it%20continues%20to%20race%20against%20rivals%20such%20as%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBard%20can%20now%20retrieve%20information%20from%20YouTube%2C%20Maps%2C%20and%20Google's%20Flights%20and%20Shopping%20search%20features.%20Also%2C%20if%20granted%20permission%2C%20it%20can%20access%20information%20from%20users'%20personal%20content%20from%20Gmail%2C%20Docs%2C%20and%20Drive%20to%20summarize%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20says%20you%20can%20ask%20Bard%20to%20find%20and%20bring%20together%20information%20from%20relevant%20emails.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20could%20ask%20it%20to%20pull%20together%20emails%20related%20to%20a%20coming%20vacation%20and%20summarize%20that%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20set%20to%20combine%20extensions%2C%20too.%20You%20could%20ask%20Bard%20to%20find%20a%20document%20you%20previously%20created%20of%20your%20bucket-list%20restaurants%20and%20then%20show%20their%20locations%20on%20a%20map.%20Or%20you%20could%20upload%20a%20photo%20to%20Lens%20and%20ask%20it%20to%20find%20relevant%20YouTube%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20added%20features%20are%20the%20result%20of%20a%20new%20version%20of%20Google's%20PaLM%202%20large%20language%20model.%20Sissie%20Hsiao%2C%20a%20Google%20vice%20president%20who%20is%20the%20general%20manager%20of%20Assistant%20and%20Bard%2C%20says%20the%20new%20version%20has%20better%20fine-tuning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHsiao%20told%20Insider%20the%20information%20taken%20from%20apps%20such%20as%20Gmail%20or%20Docs%20would%20not%20be%20used%20for%20advertising%20or%20for%20training%20Google's%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20abilities%20are%20a%20big%20step%20forward%20for%20Google's%20chatbot%20and%20serve%20as%20a%20reminder%20of%20the%20advantage%20companies%20such%20as%20Google%20have%20in%20the%20AI%20race.%20Google%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-products-with-over-1-billion-users-whats-next-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enine%20products%20with%20over%201%20billion%20users%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it's%20eagerly%20weaving%20AI%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20really%20the%20first%20step%20in%20taking%20an%20LLM%20and%20not%20just%20as%20a%20text%20model%2C%20but%20actually%20bringing%20it%20into%20what%20we%20call%20agentive%20capabilities%2C%26quot%3B%20Hsiao%20said%2C%20likening%20the%20updated%20Bard%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20assistant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20been%20working%20fast%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-new-coding-features-bard-chatbot-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eiterate%20Bard%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20company%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20arrival%20of%20ChatGPT%20last%20year.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ad-ai-chatgpt-rival-bard-gives-inaccurate-answer-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBard%20had%20a%20tough%20start%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20Google%20has%20moved%20quickly%20on%20improving%20the%20chatbot's%20capabilities%20in%20recent