-research%2Fglobal-economy-business%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENYU's%20Stern%20Economic%20Outlook%20Forum%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20what%20we've%20seen%2C%20especially%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20is%20strongly%20supportive%20of%20our%20soft%20landing%20views%2C%26quot%3B%20Hatzius%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20economists%20are%20feeling%20good%20about%20the%20economy%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20labor%20market%20is%20still%20strong%20but%20cooling%20down%20to%20more%20sustainable%20levels%2C%20which%20is%20exactly%20what%20the%20Fed%20wants%20to%20see.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-us-unemployment-rate-labor-market-2023-8%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0climbed%20a%20bit%2C%20from%203.5%25%20in%20July%20to%203.8%25%20in%20August%2C%20but%20the%20bulk%20of%20that%20increase%20was%20from%20people%20coming%20off%20the%20sidelines%20and%20re-entering%20the%20the%20labor%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJob%20growth%20has%20slowed%20through%20the%20summer%2C%20but%20remains%20higher%20than%20the%20pre-pandemic%20average.%20Nick%20Bunker%2C%20economic%20research%20director%20for%20North%20America%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20told%20Insider%20after%20the%20labor%20market%20report%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20job%20growth%2C%20and%20wage%20growth%2C%20has%20broadly%20been%20trending%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDirectionally%2C%20the%20data's%20moving%20in%20a%20way%20that%20the%20Fed%20would%20like%20to%20see%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20quite%20at%20the%20levels%20they're%20probably%20comfortable%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20Bunker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJulia%20Pollak%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20told%20Insider%C2%A0that%20she%20believes%20the%20Fed%20would%20%26quot%3Bbe%20very%20pleased%26quot%3B%20with%20that%20BLS%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20might%20suggest%20that%20yes%2C%20raising%20interest%20rates%20slowed%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20but%20that%20slowing%20came%20mostly%20in%20the%20form%20of%20declining%20openings%2C%20not%20job%20losses%20and%20rising%20unemployment%2C%26quot%3B%20Pollak%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJob%20openings%20have%20cooled%20over%20the%20last%20year.%20There%20were%20about%2011.4%20million%20job%20openings%20in%20July%202022%20but%208.8%20million%20openings%20this%20past%20July.%20That%20makes%20it%20the%20lowest%20number%20of%20monthly%20openings%20so%20far%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHatzius%20also%20said%20at%20the%20NYU%20forum%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe've%20seen%20a%20very%20substantial%20rebalancing%20of%20the%20labor%20market.%26quot%3B%20Powell%20also%20pointed%20out%20the%20rebalancing%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fnewsevents%2Fspeech%2Fpowell20230825a.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espeech%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Jackson%20Hole%20Economic%20Symposium%20but%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bremains%20incomplete.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20rebalancing%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20has%20taken%20place%20in%20a%20very%20painless%20kind%20of%20fashion%20via%20big%20declines%20in%20job%20openings%2C%20with%20very%20little%20increase%20in%20the%20unemployment%20rate%2C%20and%20very%20little%20decrease%20in%20employment%20relative%20to%20the%20labor%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20Hatzius%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20mixed%20outlook%20on%20the%20next%2012%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHatzius%20said%20Goldman%20Sachs%20sees%20GDP%20growth%20at%201.9%25%20next%20year%20while%20expecting%20only%20a%2015%25%20chance%20of%20a%20recession%20in%20the%20next%2012%20months.%20Hatzius%20said%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bdrag%20from%20monetary%20policy%20tightening%20that%20operates%20via%20tighter%20financial%20conditions%20is%20largely%20in%20the%20past.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20seen%20clear%20evidence%20that%20inflation%20is%20moving%20down%20to%20the%20Fed's%20target%2C%20or%20strongly%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20Fed's%20target%2C%20without%20a%20substantial%20deterioration%20in%20the%20real%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Hatzius%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20think%20the%20real%20economy%20is%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20perform%20reasonably%20solidly%20with%20some%20ups%20and%20downs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20strong%20real%20disposable%20household%20income%20continues%20to%20grow%2C%20which%20will%20push%20the%20economy%20forward%20even%20more%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichelle%20Meyer%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20Mastercard%20US%2C%20said%20at%20the%20NYU%20forum%20that%20the%20consumer%20%26quot%3Bis%20taking%20back%20some%20of%20their%20power.%26quot%3B%20Yet%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20consumer%20now%20is%20being%20a%20lot%20more%20mindful%20of%20how%20they%20are%20spending%20and%20engaging%20in%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Meyer%20said%2C%20as%20consumers%20don't%20have%20the%20same%20kind%20of%20excess%20savings%20they%C2%A0built%20up%20during%20the%20pandemic%C2%A0amid%20generous%20government%20stimulus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20entering%20a%20period%20where%20consumers%20are%20returning%20to%20an%20environment%20where%20they're%20much%20more%20dependent%20on%20the%20path%20of%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20on%20the%20flow%20of%20income%20creation%2C%26quot%3B%20Meyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20major%20events%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economic-outlook-2024-risks-signs-struggle-torsten-slok-2023-9%5C%22%3Ecould%20hit%20the%20American%20consumer%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20next%20few%20months%20will%20force%20the%20Fed%20to%20think%20carefully%20about%20its%20upcoming%20interest%20rate%20decisions%20and%20whether%20another%20hike%20is%20in%20the%20cards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20pressing%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%