ield%20curve%20%E2%80%93%20when%20short-dated%20Treasurys%20offer%20a%20higher%20return%20than%20longer-term%20Treasurys%20%E2%80%93%20is%20typically%20seen%20by%20investors%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20looming%20economic%20weakness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20banks%2C%20which%20make%20money%20by%20borrowing%20bonds%20at%20typically%20low%20short-term%20rates%20and%20lend%20them%20out%20to%20businesses%20at%20higher%20long-term%20rates%2C%20have%20little%20motive%20to%20lend%20when%20short-term%20rates%20are%20so%20high.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2010-year%20and%203-month%20yield%20curve%20has%20been%20inverted%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Frecession-indicator-economic-outlook-alarm-bond-market-record-yield-curve-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E212%20trading%20days%20in%20a%20row%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20the%20longest%20stretch%20since%20at%20least%201962%2C%20Bloomberg%20data%20shows.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20fear%20of%20a%20recession%20isn't%20what's%20driving%20an%20inversion%20of%20the%20yield%20curve.%20In%20fact%2C%20longer-term%20Treasury%20yields%20have%20jumped%20as%20markets%20price%20in%20a%20lower%20possibility%20of%20an%20economic%20downturn%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goldmansachs.com%2Fintelligence%2Fpages%2Fwhy-the-yield-curve-isnt-signalling-recession.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Ashok%20Varadhan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20co-head%20of%20global%20banking%20%26amp%3B%20markets%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20in%20a%20%26quot%3BGoldman%20Sachs%20Exchanges%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goldmansachs.com%2Fintelligence%2Fpodcasts%2Fepisodes%2Fnormalizing-inflation-are-hard-yards-ahead.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%20episode%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Varadhan%20said%20a%20restrictive%20Federal%20Reserve%20policy%20is%20fueling%20an%20inverted%20yield%20curve.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20yield%20curve%20is%20less%20inverted%20than%20it%20has%20been.%20So%2C%20I'd%20say%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20last%20two%20months%20as%20the%20market%20has%20basically%20taken%20down%20its%20probability%20of%20a%20recession%2C%26quot%3B%20Varadhan%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20what%20I%20would%20say%20is%20it's%20inverted%20because%20people%20still%20feel%20on%20a%20long%20run%20basis%20the%20policy%20rate%20is%20restrictive.%20We're%20in%20a%20restrictive%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%2C%20people%20believe%20that%20will%20mean%20revert%20over%20time%20back%20to%20what%20I%20said%20before%2C%20you%20know%2C%20sort%20of%20a%20long-term%20neutral%20rate%20of%2C%20call%20it%2C%203.5%20percent.%20So%2C%20therefore%2C%20that's%20what's%20driving%20the%20inversion%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-economy-outlook-inflation-recession-goldman-sachs-interest-rates-risk-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edialed%20back%20its%20prediction%20a%20US%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20bullish%20view%20compared%20to%20the%20wider%20markets%20landscape%2C%20recently%20forecasting%20that%20the%20Fed%20may%20appears%20to%20have%20beaten%20back%20inflation%20and%20skirted%20an%20economic%20slowdown%20for%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-indicator-isnt-signalling-recession-yield-curve-goldman-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695115581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6399ba3827c0a700193e0bf7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Frecession-indicator-isnt-signalling-recession-yield-curve-goldman-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20the%20Wall%20Street%20bank%2C%20a%20restrictive%20Federal%20Reserve%20policy%20is%20what's%20driving%20an%20inversion%20in%20the%20yield%20curve%2C%20not%20recession%20fears.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ztayeb%40businessinsider.com%20(Zahra%20Tayeb)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Frecession-indicator-isnt-signalling-recession-yield-curve-goldman-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22America%20is%20stuck%20in%20a%20greased-pig%20economy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222404%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bankers%20wrestling%20a%20piggy%20bank%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6508765ff05aa00019be4fef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221206%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerica%20has%20been%20living%20in%20an%20economic%20version%20of%20the%20greased-pig%20game%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20we%20lose%20our%20grip%20on%20inflation%2C%20things%20could%20get%20ugly.%3Cp%3ELiam%20Eisenberg%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETrying%20to%20catch%20a%20greased%20pig%20is%20an%20American%20tradition%20that%20has%20fallen%20out%20of%20fashion%20%E2%80%94%20so%20you're%20forgiven%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20the%20rules.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20game%2C%20once%20a%20staple%20of%20county%20and%20state%20fairs%2C%20is%20simple%20enough%3A%20A%20small%20pig%20is%20covered%20in%20lubricant%20and%20thrown%20into%20a%20ring%20where%20contestants%20try%20to%20catch%20the%20animal.%20What%20makes%20it%20hard%20%E2%80%94%20and%20fun%20to%20watch%20for%20spectators%20%E2%80%94%20is%20that%20pigs%20are%20shiftier%20than%20lumbering%20humans.%20Just%20when%20you%20think%20you%20have%20a%20grip%20on%20them%2C%20the%20slick%20porker%20can%20slip%20through%20your%20fingers.%20And%20when%20it's%20all%20over%2C%20both%20pig%20and%20human%20end%20up%20dirty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20pandemic%2C%20America%20has%20been%20living%20in%20an%20economic%20version%20of%20the%20greased-pig%20game%20%E2%80%94%20prices%20have%20been%20running%20free%20despite%20assurances%20from%20policymakers%20and%20economists%20that%20the%20pig%20(inflation)%20will%20be%20caught%20soon%2C%20which%20is%20to%20say%2C%20brought%20down%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%202%25%20target.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20we%20may%20have%20finally%20caught%20the%20pig.%20The%20consumer%20price%20index%2C%20the%20most-watched%20measure%20of%20inflation%2C%20was%20moving%20downward%20smoothly.%20At%20the%20same%20time%20that%20prices%20were%20cooling%20off%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20economy%20seemed%20to%20be%20holding%20up.%20The%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-us-unemployment-rate-labor-market-2023-8%5C%22%3E%20labor%20market%20was%20healthy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Until%20August%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-rally-outlook-nvidia-morgan-stanley-jpmorgan-wall-street-2023-8%5C%22%3Estock%20market%20had%20been%20staging%20a%20glorious%20rally%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20consumers%20were%20so%20intent%20on%20spending%20money%20to%20have%20a%20good%20time%20that%20cities%20let%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbeyonce-paid-keep-trains-running-extra-hour-severe-weather-washington-2023-8%5C%22%3EBeyonc%C3%A9%20dictate%20public%20transit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20as%20greased%20pigs%20are%20unpredictable%2C%20so%20is%20inflation.%20August's%20CPI%20release%20showed%20that%20inflation%20increased%203.7%25%20from%20the%20same%20time%20last%20year%2C%20higher%20than%20July's%20print%20of%203.2%25%20and%20a%20tick%20above%20analysts'%20expectations%20of%203.6%25.%20This%20increase%20was%20mostly%20due%20to%20rising%20energy%20prices%2C%20but%20even%20core%20inflation%2C%20which%20strips%20out%20volatile%20categories%20like%20energy%20and%20food%2C%20showed%20signs%20of%20heating%20back%20up.%20Core%20CPI%20registered%204.3%25%20year-over-year%20%E2%80%94%20much%20improved%20from%20its%20peak%20of%206.6%25%20in%20September%202022%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20increased%200.3%25%20on%20a%20month-to-month%20basis%2C%20higher%20than%20the%20Wall%20Street%20consensus.%20This%20pig%20doesn't%20run%20in%20a%20straight%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20greased-pig%20economy%2C%20stability%20depends%20on%20how%20confident%20investors%20and%20policymakers%20are%20that%20they're%20close%20to%20catching%20the%20pig.%20A%20lack%20of%20certainty%20opens%20up%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20questions%20about%20the%20future.%20Such%20as%20what%20happens%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20ugly%20will%20things%20get%20%E2%80%94%20if%20the%20pig%20manages%20to%20slip%20out%20of%20our%20arms%3F%20What%20will%20the%20economy%20look%20like%20if%20the%20chase%20gets%20prolonged%3F%20How%20dirty%20will%20we%20have%20to%20get%20to%20actually%20catch%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20lose%20our%20grip%20on%20inflation%2C%20it%20means%20interest%20rates%20will%20surely%20have%20to%20stay%20higher%20for%20longer%20%E2%80%94%20tightening%20financial%20conditions%20for%20consumers%2C%20governments%2C%20and%20businesses.%20Consumers%20will%20eventually%20stop%20spending%20and%20lower%20corporate%20profits%20will%20hurt%20the%20stock%20market.%20It%20means%20a%20sagging%20economy%2C%20or%20even%20a%20recession%2C%20is%20still%20on%20the%20table.%20It%20means%20there%20is%20still%20room%20for%20central%20banks%20to%20make%20an%20error%2C%20slip%2C%20and%20fall%20in%20the%20mud%20while%20the%20pig%20keeps%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMoving%20in%20a%20mess%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20messy%20economy%20the%20pandemic%20left%20us%2C%20it's%20not%20easy%20to%20pinpoint%20exactly%20why%20inflation%20has%20been%20so%20stubborn.%20On%20an%20Economy%20101%20level%2C%20inflation%20occurs%20when%20demand%20for%20goods%20or%20services%20outstrips%20the%20ability%20to%20supply%20or%20produce%20those%20goods%20and%20services%20%E2%80%94%20the%20pandemic%20threw%20both%20sides%20of%20that%20equation%20out%20of%20whack.%20Supply%20was%20limited%20by%20factory%20shutdowns%2C%20supply-chain%20snarls%2C%20and%20business%20closures.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20demand%20was%20higher%20thanks%20to%20stimulus%20checks%2C%20boosted%20savings%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fluxury-industry-loses-billions-pandemic-radically-transformed-2021-4%5C%22%3Erevenge%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20mismatch%20in%20what%20people%20wanted%20versus%20what%20the%20economy%20was%20able%20to%20produce%20pushed%20up%20prices%20for%20everything%20from%20cars%20and%20washing%20machines%20to%20airfare%20and%20a%20drink%20at%20a%20bar.%20And%20despite%20assurances%20from%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20and%20others%20that%20this%20was%20a%20short-term%20rebalancing%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20it%20was%20the%20start%20of%20a%20now%20three-year-long%20chase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20done%20everything%20it%20can%20to%20try%20and%20get%20the%20inflation%20pig%20back%20in%20the%20pen%2C%20and%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20it%20appeared%20like%20it%20was%20closing%20in%20on%20its%20goal.%20CPI%20inflation%20peaked%20at%209%25%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fcea%2Fwritten-materials%2F2023%2F05%2F10%2Fthe-signal-and-the-noise-part-ii-cpi-inflation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJune%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20been%20going%20down%20steadily%20since.%20Many%20economists%20predicted%20that%20the%20Fed%20would%20have%20to%20crush%20the%20demand%20side%20of%20the%20equation%20in%20order%20to%20wrangle%20inflation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20crushing%20demand%20eventually%20would%20mean%20hurting%20the%20labor%20market%20as%20companies%20size%20down%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20business.%20But%20Mike%20Konczal%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20left-leaning%20Roosevelt%20Institute%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frooseveltinstitute.org%2Fpublications%2Fsupply-side-expansion-has-driven-the-decline-in-inflation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eargued%20in%20a%20recent%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20main%20driver%20of%20the%20recent%20disinflation%20has%20been%20the%20normalization%20of%20the%20supply%20side.%20As%20Konczal%20pointed%20out%2C%20we've%20seen%20a%20decline%20in%20prices%20despite%20a%20strong%20labor%20market%20and%20consumer%20demand.%20So%20the%20decline%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20must%20be%20coming%20from%20the%20supply%20side%20%E2%80%94%20businesses%20are%20finally%20being%20able%20to%20get%20people%20the%20products%20they%20need%20without%20a%20problem.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EBut%20just%20as%20greased%20pigs%20are%20unpredictable%2C%20so%20is%20inflation.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20pig%20chase%20isn't%20over.%20Normalizing%20things%20on%20the%20supply%20side%20has%20been%20a%20slow%20process%2C%20but%20in%20many%20respects%20that%20was%20the%20easy%20part%20%E2%80%94%20businesses%20want%20to%20get%20their%20production%20going%20again.%20But%20with%20inflation%20still%20above%20the%20Fed's%20goal%2C%20it's%20clear%20we%20need%20to%20recalibrate%20some%20on%20the%20demand%20side%20still.%20That%20means%20we%20may%20be%20entering%20the%20messiest%2C%20most%20slippery%20phase%20yet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20higher-than-desired%20headline%20and%20core%20CPI%20numbers%2C%20there%20are%20also%20other%20signs%20that%20prices%20may%20be%20reaccelerating.%20Take%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bsupercore%26quot%3B%20CPI%2C%20which%20strips%20out%20housing%20costs%20in%20addition%20to%20energy%20and%20food%20prices%20to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20the%20underlying%20inflation%20rate%20for%20common%20service%20businesses.%20The%20measure%2C%20which%20has%20attracted%20increased%20attention%20from%20the%20Fed%2C%20accelerated%20to%200.37%25%20on%20a%20month-over-month%20basis%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20reading%20since%20March.%20And%20the%20Producer%20Price%20Index%2C%20which%20tries%20to%20track%20what%20companies%20are%20paying%20for%20the%20stuff%20they%20need%20to%20run%20their%20businesses%2C%20jumped%20by%200.7%25%20in%20August%2C%20the%20hottest%20reading%20since%20June%202022%20and%20well%20above%20the%200.4%25%20increase%20expected%20by%20economists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20reason%20to%20doubt%20our%20grip%20on%20prices%20is%20the%20American%20consumer.%20But%20given%20Americans'%20proclivity%20to%20spend%2C%20it%20will%20be%20tougher%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20painful%20%E2%80%94%20to%20catch%20this%20pig%20on%20the%20demand%20side.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20so%20far%20tried%20to%20put%20a%20damper%20on%20demand%20by%20hiking%20interest%20rates%20from%200%25%20to%20over%205%25%2C%20making%20money%20more%20expensive.%20Consumers%20have%20been%20strong%20enough%20to%20bear%20these%20increased%20borrowing%20costs%20and%2C%20on%20one%20hand%2C%20that's%20been%20good%20news.%20But%20on%20the%20other%2C%20their%20desire%20to%20spend%20every%20last%20dollar%20on%20Taylor%20Swift%20tickets%20is%20making%20this%20pig%20harder%20to%20catch.%20The%20latest%20CPI%20report%20showed%20that%20prices%20for%20food%20away%20from%20home%20(a%20proxy%20for%20eating%20out%20at%20restaurants)%20increased%206.5%25%20from%20the%20year%20before%2C%20while%20transportation%20services%20(think%20cabs%2C%20Ubers%2C%20etc.)%20were%20up%2010.3%25.%20If%20we%20know%20anything%20about%20this%20pig%2C%20it's%20that%20it%20likes%20to%20party.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20pig%20slips%20away%20and%20inflation%20does%20start%20meaningfully%20rising%20again%2C%20the%20Fed%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20resume%20its%20interest-rate%20hikes.%20The%20longer%20rates%20stay%20high%2C%20the%20longer%20financial%20conditions%20are%20tighter%20or%20tightening%2C%20the%20more%20strain%20we'll%20see%20on%20the%20consumer%20and%20on%20businesses.%20This%20is%20the%20scenario%20some%20economists%20worried%20about%3A%20that%20by%20hiking%20rates%20too%20high%20and%20sucking%20money%20away%20from%20consumers%20and%20businesses%2C%20the%20Fed%20could%20tip%20us%20into%20recession.%20That's%20when%20we'd%20see%20layoffs%20and%20stock-market%20malaise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20clear%20that%20the%20Fed%20and%20other%20central%20banks%20are%20keeping%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20this%20possibility.%20Chicago%20Fed%20president%20Charles%20Evans%20said%20that%20if%20it%20meant%20finally%20wrestling%20inflation%20down%2C%20he'd%20rather%20overshoot%20interest-rate%20hikes%20and%20have%20a%20mild%20slowdown%20than%20slip%20into%20stagflation.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20European%20Central%20Bank%20raised%20rates%20last%20week%2C%20despite%20recession%20fears%20on%20the%20continent.%20%26quot%3BInflation%20has%20declined%2C%20and%20we%20want%20it%20to%20continue%20to%20decline%20and%20to%20reinforce%20that%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20ECB%20president%20Christine%20Lagarde%20explained%20at%20a%20presser%20following%20the%20decision.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20are%20doing%20that%20not%20because%20we%20want%20to%20force%20a%20recession%2C%20but%20because%20we%20want%20price%20stability%20to%20be%20there%20for%20people%20who%20are%20taking%20the%20brunt%20of%20inflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPocket%20reality%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20chance%20that%20this%20all%20works%20itself%20out%20on%20its%20own.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20JP%20Morgan%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%20said%20that%20the%20consumer%20will%20eventually%20run%20out%20of%20steam%2C%20exhausting%20accumulated%20pandemic%20savings%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fjpmorgan-jamie-dimon-consumer-spending-economy-recession-inflation-war-food-2023-7%5C%22%3Eby%20Christmas.%3C%2Fa%3E%20If%20the%20Roosevelt%20Institute's%20Konczal%20is%20correct%2C%20that%20will%20have%20to%20happen%20for%20inflation%20to%20go%20down.%20In%20the%20best-case%20scenario%2C%20this%20gradual%20slowdown%20will%20be%20enough%20to%20catch%20the%20pig%20for%20real%3A%20The%20supply%20side%20will%20be%20healed%2C%20while%20consumer%20demand%20cools%20off%20just%20enough%20to%20keep%20things%20level%20%E2%80%94%20a%20soft%20landing.%20However%2C%20the%20longer%20the%20Fed's%20hiking%20cycle%20persists%20%E2%80%94%20the%20longer%20the%20chase%20goes%20on%20%E2%80%94%20the%20more%20likely%20the%20landing%20will%20be%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThis%20isn't%20horseshoes%20or%20hand%20grenades%2C%20it's%20pig%20wrestling%20%E2%80%94%20close%20is%20not%20good%20enough.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20summer%20of%20hope%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20this%20chase%20to%20end%20badly%20is%20clearly%20weighing%20on%20investors'%20minds%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20more%20worried%20investors%20get%2C%20the%20more%20skittish%20they%20are.%20Uncertain%20investors%20tend%20to%20start%20asking%20more%20questions%2C%20such%20as%3A%20Just%20how%20accurately%20are%20the%20Fed's%20models%20tracking%20real-life%20experiences%3F%20What%20happens%20if%20they%20misread%20what%20gas%20prices%20are%20doing%20to%20people's%20pockets%20and%20hike%20too%20little%20or%20too%20much%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20you're%20going%20to%20start%20seeing%20is%20the%20investing%20public%20saying%2C%20'Hey%2C%20you've%20stripped%20so%20much%20out%20of%20core%20inflation%20that%20it%20no%20longer%20represents%20how%20humans%20interact%20with%20the%20economy%2C'%26quot%3B%20Justin%20Simon%2C%20a%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20the%20hedge%20fund%20Jasper%20Capital%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELest%20you%20forget%20why%20we're%20chasing%20this%20pig%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FbyHeatherLong%2Fstatus%